  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1 \u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "India supports a political solution in Sri Lanka as soon as possible in line with democratic principles",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Indian High Commission in Sri Lanka has announced that India will provide full support for a speedy political solution in Sri Lanka in accordance with democratic principles and the constitution.",
        "Apart from that, the High Commission has also stated that it completely denies the reports that India helped the former President to leave or travel to Sri Lanka in any way.",
        "At the same time, the High Commission reaffirmed that India will always stand with the people of Sri Lanka to achieve the aspirations of the people aimed at prosperity and development in accordance with democratic principles, democratic structures and the constitution.",
        "Commenting on a press conference held on Thursday (14), the spokesperson of the Indian Ministry of External Affairs said that India expects a speedy solution to the situation related to the government and its leadership in Sri Lanka in accordance with democratic ideals, democratic structures and the constitution. The spokesperson of India's Ministry of External Affairs has also assured that it is ready to help.",
        "The High Commission of India has pointed out that the assistance provided by India to the Sri Lankan people in order to solve the current prevailing challenges in Sri Lanka underlines the principles of India's 'Neighborhood First' and Security and Development (SAGAR) for all countries in the region.",
        "It is also noteworthy that the High Commission, which has indicated that India has provided assistance worth 3.8 billion US dollars to help the people of Sri Lanka to recover from the economic crisis, has also announced that it has completely denied the reports that India helped the former president to leave or travel to Sri Lanka in any way."
      ],
